duit1998 wrote:
&gt; The method SimpleTestCollector.isTestClass(String classFileName) is
&gt; implemented faulty:
&gt;
&gt; This is the implementation of junit 3.8.1:
&gt; protected boolean isTestClass(String classFileName) {
&gt;       return
&gt;             classFileName.endsWith(&quot;.class&quot;) &&
&gt;             classFileName.indexOf(&#39;$&#39;) &lt; 0 &&
&gt;             classFileName.indexOf(&quot;Test&quot;) &gt; 0;
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; Using this implementation a test method will not be recognized if it
&gt; starts with the term &quot;test&quot; (any case) becaus String.indexOf returns
&gt; -1 if no substring &quot;test&quot; could be found. If the method name starts
&gt; with &quot;test&quot; String.indexOf returns 0. However, the implementation
&gt; quoted above returns FALSE although the substring &quot;test&quot; could be
&gt; found!. Thus, we have to change the last LOC to test fpr &gt;= 0:
&gt;
&gt; classFileName.indexOf(&quot;Test&quot;) &gt; 0;
&gt;
&gt; Now it works.
&gt;
&gt; Where is the place to post this so that this bug will be cleared?
&gt; (...though I could not believe to be the first to find out about this.)
&gt;
&gt; Dirk
